<title type="html"><![CDATA[Is VRC7's CHR-RAM bankswitched?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6420&amp;p=62048#p62048"><![CDATA[
In fact mode 0 simply enables normal attribute tables, while mode 1 enable extended attributes tables. The mode 1 can read both color and tile data from the same area, but doing so will be impractical and useless.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Sat May 29, 2010 12:03 pm</p><hr />
