Thank you!<br /><br />I have another, unrelated question (no point in starting a new topic): concerning MMC5's EXRAM, what's the effective difference between the third nametable in mode 0 and mode 1? It seems that mode 0 doesn't allow for extended attributes, but judging by being able to set nametable mapping at $5105 to %10 in mode 1 it seems that mode 1 can provide an extra nametable <em>and</em> extended attributes at the same time. How is this possible with the same 1KB of RAM? I'm assuming that concessions have to be made somewhere to make it work. But how can mode 1's nametable be "inferior" to mode 0's (or do the extended attributes take a hit somehow)?<br /><br />Also, if the EXRAM can't be written to in mode 3, what advantage does it have over mode 2...?<br /><br />Thank you again!  <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4395">The Most Curious Thing</a> — Fri May 28, 2010 8:33 am</p><hr />
